for &quot;Cn&quot;(&quot;z&quot;) and &quot;Dn&quot;(&quot;z&quot;) with integer coefficients, &quot;Cn&quot;(&quot;z&quot;) of degree &quot;φ&quot;(&quot;n&quot;), and &quot;Dn&quot;(&quot;z&quot;) of degree &quot;φ&quot;(&quot;n&quot;) − 1. &quot;Cn&quot;(&quot;z&quot;) and &quot;Dn&quot;(&quot;z&quot;) are both palindromic.

